            <title>[SPARK-3084] Collect broadcasted tables in parallel in joins</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-3084</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;BroadcastHashJoin has a broadcastFuture variable that tries to collect the broadcasted table in a separate thread, but this doesn&apos;t help because it&apos;s a lazy val that only gets initialized when you attempt to build the RDD. Thus queries that broadcast multiple tables would collect and broadcast them sequentially.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
